M2 micro framework by Alexander Chaika (marco.manti@gmail.com).

Source link: https://github.com/marco-manti/M2_micro/

Current version: 0.3RC4

Requirements: 

    PHP 5.3+, MySQL 5.0+, MySQLi PHP driver.


Installation at Ubuntu: 

1. Create directory "source": 
    $ mkdir source

2. Clone source code from github: 
    $ git clone https://github.com/marco-manti/M2_micro.git ./source

3. Create config file from sample and edit it:
    $ cp ./source/trunk/includes/config.ini.sample ./source/trunk/includes/config.ini

4. Create "log" and "tmp" directories and set privilegies:
    $ mkdir log tmp
    $ chmod 777 log tmp

5. Create new apache2 host:
    $ sudo gedit /etc/apache2/sites-available/m2.local

6. And put this:

    <VirtualHost 127.0.0.1:80>
      DocumentRoot "/home/user/Projects/manti/m2_micro/source/trunk"
      ServerName "m2.local"
      ServerAlias "*.m2.local"

      ErrorLog "/home/user/Projects/manti/m2_micro/log/apache_error.log"
      CustomLog "/home/user/Projects/manti/log/apache_access.log" combined

      php_value error_log "/home/user/Projects/manti/m2_micro/log/php_error.log"
      php_value session.save_path "/home/user/Projects/manti/m2_micro/tmp"
      php_value upload_tmp_dir "/home/user/Projects/manti/m2_micro/tmp"

      Alias "/help" "/home/user/Projects/manti/m2_micro/source/docs/phpdoc"
      Alias "/stat" "/home/user/Projects/manti/m2_micro/source/docs/pdepend"
    </VirtualHost>
    
7. Create symlink for host:
    $ ln -s /etc/apache2/sites-available/m2.local /etc/apache2/sites-enabled/m2.local
    
    
8. Deploy database

    8.1. You can use already compiled DB from file ./source/database/database.sql.
    
    8.2. Or you can create "clean" database from migrations in ./source/database/. 
         For this you need use "Database migration tool", you can find it in ./source/utils
         directory, to run it simply call:
         $ db-migrate.sh    # or from windows > db-migrate.bat
    
9. Create HOSTS record:
    $ sudo gedit /etc/hosts

    and add lines bellow
    
    127.0.0.1   m2.local
    127.0.0.1   www.m2.local
    
10. Also in latest version uses Memecache server to speed up some operations. You can choose default
    cache type in ./source/trunk/includes/cache.php:51.

11. Restart apache2 and enjoy! Open your browser and go to http://m2.local.

